Data.Content:
Grid Map Data Structures:
- Define:
  enum CellState { CELL_UNKNOWN = 0, CELL_FREE = 1, CELL_BLOCKED = 2 };
  enum WallState { WALL_UNKNOWN = 0, WALL_PRESENT = 1, WALL_ABSENT = 2 };
  enum ReturnToStartStatusEnum { RETURN_NOT_EXECUTED = 0, RETURN_SUCCESS = 1, RETURN_FAILURE = 2 };
  enum SecondRunStatusEnum { SECOND_RUN_NOT_EXECUTED = 0, SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS = 1, SECOND_RUN_FAILURE = 2 };
- Cell storage:
  CellState cells[4][8];
- Wall storage:
  - Horizontal walls between (row, col) and (row+1, col):
    WallState hWalls[3][8];
  - Vertical walls between (row, col) and (row, col+1):
    WallState vWalls[4][7];
- Coordinate convention (example):
  - Row 0, Col 0 is start cell at bottom-left or a specified corner, as per HL environment.
  All modules must consistently use this indexing.
